(In reply to comment #1) > thanks for all the changes Jens !
NP :)
> (can I ask what's the advanteges of yui over jquery?
Yes, of course.
> google and lots of other > companies are using jquery over yui,
Well, that doesn't says much as well as that Microsoft/Nokia took "ownership" of it ;-). Not sure, whether "over yui" applies at all - I can imagine, that they just tried jQuery (because there seems to be a kind of hype right now) and because it fits their needs, they didn't look around for anything else ...
> so why do we want to move away ? :)
First: I think any JS framework can be used to accomplish the required stuff. But the question is: where you wanna go?
I see jQuery more or less like PHP in its early days: a very loosely coupled collection of perl scripts and YUI like Java ~ 1.3.
I.e. if one just needs to quickly hack something, jQuery is IMHO ok. But if one wanna write long living, maintainable applications, jQuery gets quickly out of scope - one needs more than just a little bit of "syntactic sugar". And here YUI slips in: One can simply extend the framework and keep its own bits separately (as shown with the symbols panel), i.e. usually no need to hack the framework itself and thus can take advantage of updates/fixes without much trouble. Also it is probably a better choice for test adiccted developers (e.g. YUI Yeti) ;-). That's basically it (there is much more, but probably needs hours to write it down ;-)).
Some IMHO valuable links I've found for this are: http://dsheiko.com/weblog/yui3-vs-jquery http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x0OuYNlnCZ8&feature=youtube_gdata_player http://yuilibrary.com/theater/
